Debugging on Eclipse
	
1- Configure the eclipse debugger

	2.1 - Create a new GDB Hardware Debugging configuration
		2.1.1 - Select the project and the application(.elf ?????????)
		2.1.2 - Set the following options in the Debug tab:
				GDB command: avr-gdb
				JTAG device: Generic
				Host: localhost
				Port: 4242
		2.1.3 - In the Startup tab unmark everything except the Resume option in the Resume Options frame.
		
2 - Start the gdb server over the jtagice:
	
	sudo avarice --mkII --ignore-intr --jtag usb :4242
	

3- Run the debug configuration you created